reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No more noise, good product
reviews.reviewText: The old serpentine belt of my 2006 chrysler town and country was very noisy and I figured it was time to be replaced. I chose Bando because it has a very good reputation on the online forums (and it turns out to have a fair price). So far it's been working great, no more squeaks coming from the serpentine belt. It's always a good idea to change the belt tensioner and the idler with the belt itself, so I also replaced them and so far everything is working fine. BE CAREFUL not to buy a tensioner pulley (smaller) thinking it is the idler (bigger), their sizes are different and you should NOT install the tensioner pulley as the idler.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I replaced this belt on a 2013 Subaru outback with the 2.5 liter engine. I noticed the 2013 model has a slightly different layout to models that are a year or 2 older a 2011 model for example has one idler pulley while the 2013 has 2. So definitely something to be aware of so you get the correct part. From my understanding and some research I've done this is the OEM supplier for the 2013 Subaru outback. It feels well made and was the perfect fit. It doesn't make any noise whatsoever but I also did replace the idler pulleys and tensioner on the car so all of those components are new.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not just for autos
reviews.reviewText: I used this on a zero turn lawnmower as a replacement for my drive belt (not the pulley belt). The drive belt is more or less flat as opposed to being V shaped. Had difficulties finding the exact belt replacement, so opted for the serpentine belt. The width was too wide so just trimmed to my desired width and seems to be working fine. I know this is outside the box on lawnmower repair but seems to be the way I think sometimes.
